The `TagsFlowRow` which contains the tags, is inside the `Card`. The click event on a tag is bubbling up to the parent `Card`.

I need to read the full `BookmarkCard` implementation to apply the fix. The fix involves adding a `pointerInput` modifier to the `TagsFlowRow` to stop the event propagation to the parent. Specifically, I'll use `pointerInput(Unit) { detectTapGestures {} }` on the `FlowRow` containing the tags. This will intercept and consume the tap gesture, preventing the card's `onClick` from firing when a tag is clicked.

